Hindu Astronomy is a very ancient science. Its source-book is the ç
S<220>rya-siddh<193>nta. It was taught by S<220>rya (Sun-god) to ç
Maya (the architect of the asuras) at the end of the K<216>tayuga.
The work that is available now might have taken shape during <MS>A.<|>D.<D> ç
400. Var<193>hamihira (<MS>A.<|>D.<D> 550) made use of this work in ç
his Pa<210>casiddh<193>ntik<193>. It has three commentaries, the ç
