1360-1455) and Ra<209>gan<193>tha (<MS>A.<|>D.<D> 1640). Of these, ç
the last one is the most detailed.
The book is divided into 14 chapters.
The following is a brief summary of its contents:
@S10 = Chapter 1
It deals with the mean motion of the planets. It also gives enough ç
information to calculate the mean daily motion of the planets.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 2
The method of calculating the true position of a planet including ç
the corrections needed for its retrograde motion is given here.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 3
This chapter deals with direction, place and time. The method of constructing ç
a sun-dial is also given.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 4
Both  the  eclipses†especially  the lunar eclipse†are dealt with here.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 5
Calculations for the parallax of the solar eclipse are given here.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 6
