@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 7
Planetary conjunctions are the subject dealt with here.
@SPACE1 = 
@S10 = Chapter 8
This chapter gives the positions of the various nak<218>atras (or ç
groups of stars).
@S10 = Chapter 9
Heliacal rising and setting of the planets are described here.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 10
This gives the calculations needed to correctly state the rising and ç
setting of the moon.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 11
This is partly astrological in nature. The malignant character of ç
the time as related to the sun and the moon is given here along with ç
the necessary rules for calculating it.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 12
The theory of creation of the world is the subject-matter of this ç
section.
@SPACE = 
@S10 = Chapter 13
This deals with certain instruments needed for the determination of ç
